ing technical communication well is important because:</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>You need to work with other technical folks on projects / products</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>You need to share your work with non-technical audiences (like senior management)</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>There are two types of technical communication we focus on today:</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>Writing good technical reports for your data science work</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:pPr lvl="1"/><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>Communicating well with non-technical audiences</a:t></a:r></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp></p:spTree><p:extLst><p:ext uri="{BB962C8B-B14F-4D97-AF65-F5344CB8AC3E}"><p14:creationId xmlns:p14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/powerpoint/2010/main" val="1948515332"/></p:ext></p:extLst></p:cSld><p:clrMapOvr><a:masterClrMapping/></p:clrMapOvr></p:sld>